        <section id="sms-communications">
            <h2>SMS Communications & Text-to-Shelf Service</h2>

            <h3>Overview</h3>
            <p>When you enable the Text-to-Shelf feature on TBR.fyi, you consent to receive SMS (text) messages from us at the phone number you provide.</p>

            <h3>What Messages You'll Receive</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Verification Messages</strong> - One-time when enabling SMS<br>
                    Example: "Your TBR.fyi verification code is: 847293"</li>
                <li><strong>Book Addition Confirmations</strong> - Each time you text a book<br>
                    Example: "✓ Added to your TBR: 'The Overstory' by Richard Powers"</li>
                <li><strong>Local Availability Notifications</strong> (Optional) - When books become available<br>
                    Example: "📚 'Demon Copperhead' in stock at Powell's Books!"</li>
                <li><strong>Service Updates</strong> (Rare) - Fewer than 5 per year for critical information</li>
                <li><strong>Help Responses</strong> - Only when you text "HELP" or "INFO"</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Message Frequency</h3>
            <p>Message frequency varies based on your usage:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Verification:</strong> One-time per setup</li>
                <li><strong>Confirmations:</strong> Each time you text a book (you control this)</li>
                <li><strong>Availability Alerts:</strong> Based on inventory changes (optional, can be disabled)</li>
                <li><strong>Service Updates:</strong> Rare (fewer than 5 per year)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Typical users receive 1-10 messages per month.</p>

            <h3>Message & Data Rates</h3>
            <p>Standard message and data rates from your mobile carrier may apply. TBR.fyi does not charge for SMS messages, but your carrier may charge for receiving texts.</p>

            <h3>How to Opt-Out</h3>
            <p><strong>Method 1: Text Commands</strong><br>
            Reply to any message with: STOP, UNSUBSCRIBE, CANCEL, END, QUIT, OPTOUT, REVOKE, or STOPALL</p>

            <p><strong>Method 2: Account Settings</strong><br>
            Log into your TBR.fyi account → Profile/Settings → Disable Text-to-Shelf SMS</p>

            <p><strong>Method 3: Email</strong><br>
            Contact us at <a href="mailto:support@tbr.fyi">support@tbr.fyi</a></p>

            <p><strong>Processing Time:</strong> All opt-out requests are processed within 24 hours, typically immediately.</p>

            <h3>Third-Party Service Providers</h3>
            <p>We use <strong>Twilio</strong> as our SMS service provider. Your phone number is shared with Twilio for message delivery. Twilio processes messages according to their privacy policy: <a href="https://www.twilio.com/legal/privacy" target="_blank">https://www.twilio.com/legal/privacy</a></p>

            <h3>Data Retention (SMS)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>While SMS is enabled:</strong> For the duration of your active service</li>
                <li><strong>After opt-out:</strong> 6 months to honor your preference</li>
                <li><strong>Compliance records:</strong> 4 years per TCPA requirements</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Consent and Legal Basis</h3>
            <p>By enabling Text-to-Shelf and verifying your phone number, you provide <strong>prior express consent</strong> to receive SMS messages. This complies with:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Telephone Consumer Protection Act (TCPA)</li>
                <li>Cellular Telecommunications Industry Association (CTIA) guidelines</li>
                <li>FCC SMS regulations</li>
                <li>A2P 10DLC requirements</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

